description: Defines the 4-layer architecture (App → Features → Lib/Components). Use this rule when deciding where to place new code, creating new files, or reviewing imports between layers. Violations like a Feature importing another Feature, or Lib importing a Feature, must be flagged and fixed.
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow a strict layered architecture inspired by DDD and Separation of Concerns.

## Layers

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
|-------|----------|----------------|
| App | `src/app/` | Routing, providers, page composition |
| Features | `src/features/` | Domain-specific business logic |
| Lib | `src/lib/` | Shared utilities, framework-agnostic |
| Components | `src/components/` | Presentational UI only |

## Dependency Flow

```
App → Features → Lib / Components
```

Lower layers must never import from upper layers.

## Critical Rules

- Features must NOT import other Features directly
- Lib must NOT import from Features or Components
- Components must NOT contain business logic or API calls
- Each feature exposes a public API via `index.ts`

## Decision Guide

| Situation | Where it goes |
|-----------|---------------|
| Reusable, no business logic | `lib/` or `components/` |
| Domain-specific logic | `features/<domain>/` |
| Routing or wiring | `app/` |
